body:
I noticed that some repeatedly executed code is incorrectly put into the "__Slow" output files:

```systemverilog
module t;
  int a;
  initial forever #1 a++;
endmodule
```

Probably not going to break the world, but there might be more important cases where this propagates:

```systemverilog
module t;
  int a, b;
  initial fork forever #1 a++; forever #2 b++; join_none
endmodule
```

Generally we should only put code that is known to be executed only once in the slow files.

Maybe @kbieganski would be interested in fixing these?
